It was discovered that the Sun was governed by the same basic principles as other stars: the only factors that drove its activity within the system were its luminosity and its rotation.
The intensity of the light and the rotation are combined to calculate the Rossby number of a star, linked to the plasma flux.
The lower the Rossby number, the lower the activity of the star in relation to its magnetic inversions.
