The 802.11n standard operates on both 2.4Ghz and 5.0Ghz frequencies.
This will make it possible to be compatible with earlier versions of 802.11a, 802.11b and 802.11g, provided that the base station has dual radios.
The speeds of the 802.11n standard are much higher than those achieved by its predecessors, with a theoretical maximum throughput of 600 Mbps.
